Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat
ovener to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and mince or grate. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim
@green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

== Zesty Rice ==

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1%unit} in container before opening.

In a #small pot{}, combine @coconut milk{1/4%cup} (you'll use the rest later),
@water{1/2%cup}, @butter{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
(For 4 servings, use 1/2 cup coconut milk, 1 cup water, 2 TBSP butter, and 1 tsp sugar.)

Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}; cover, and reduce heat to
low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Patties and Green Beans ==

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%ounce},
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, ginger, @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings),
and @pepper{pinch}.

Form into 10-12 (20-24 for 4 servings) 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

Place meatballs on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Using a lightly
oiled #spatula{}, smash meatballs to make 3/4-inch-thick patties. Toss
green beans on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. (For 4
servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast patties on middle rack and green beans
on top rack.)

Roast on top rack until patties are cooked through and green beans are browned
and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Thai Chili Coconut Sauce ==

When patties and green beans have 5 minutes left, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}
with remaining @coconut milk{3/4%cup} in a #large pan{}; heat over medium-high
heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and season with salt and pepper.

Add patties to pan with coconut chili sauce; toss to coat.

Divide rice between bowls; top with patties and green beans. Spoon any remaining
sauce over patties. Sprinkle with @peanuts{1/2%ounce}. Serve with any remaining
lime wedges on the side.

> Ground turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.